  <section>
  <h2>Overview</h2>

  <p>
    This case study documents the design, implementation, and validation of a
    foundational AWS networking environment built with Terraform. The solution
    establishes a dedicated Amazon VPC with public and private subnets,
    intentional routing boundaries, internet connectivity for the public tier,
    and resource-level security controls.
  </p>

  <p>
    The project demonstrates a repeatable cloud architecture workflow that
    combines Infrastructure as Code, Architecture as Code, technical
    documentation, validation evidence, and version-controlled engineering
    decisions.
  </p>
</section>

