<section>
  <h2>Implementation Walkthrough</h2>

  <p>
    The implementation follows a staged approach so each network component can
    be understood, validated, and expanded over time.
  </p>

  <h3>1. Create the VPC</h3>
  <p>
    A dedicated VPC establishes the isolated network boundary for the
    environment and defines the primary CIDR range used by the architecture.
  </p>

  <h3>2. Define Public and Private Subnets</h3>
  <p>
    Subnets divide the VPC address space into separate network tiers. Public
    subnets support resources that require internet-facing connectivity, while
    private subnets support internal workloads.
  </p>

  <h3>3. Attach the Internet Gateway</h3>
  <p>
    The Internet Gateway enables internet connectivity for resources in public
    subnets when paired with the appropriate route table configuration.
  </p>

  <h3>4. Configure Route Tables</h3>
  <p>
  Each subnet is explicitly associated with its intended route table. Both
  route tables retain the VPC local route, while only the public route table
  includes a default route to the Internet Gateway. This creates distinct
  routing behavior without preventing permitted communication inside the VPC.
</p>

  <h3>5. Apply Security Controls</h3>
  <p>
    Security groups provide resource-level traffic control by defining allowed
    inbound and outbound communication patterns.
  </p>

  <h3>6. Validate the Design</h3>
  <p>
    The completed environment can be reviewed through Terraform output, AWS
    console verification, and connectivity testing as additional workloads are
    added.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Validation and Testing</h2>

  <p>
    The environment was validated through Terraform commands, Terraform output
    values, and inspection of the deployed resources in the AWS Management
    Console.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Ran <code>terraform fmt</code> to confirm consistent Terraform formatting.
    </li>
    <li>
      Ran <code>terraform validate</code> to confirm the configuration was
      syntactically valid and internally consistent.
    </li>
    <li>
      Reviewed the Terraform execution plan before deployment.
    </li>
    <li>
      Completed the Terraform deployment without resource-creation errors.
    </li>
    <li>
      Confirmed the VPC and subnet CIDR ranges matched the documented design.
    </li>
    <li>
      Verified the Internet Gateway was attached to the intended VPC.
    </li>
    <li>
      Confirmed the public subnet was associated with the public route table.
    </li>
    <li>
      Confirmed the private subnet was associated with the private route table.
    </li>
    <li>
      Verified the public route table contained a
      <code>0.0.0.0/0</code> route targeting the Internet Gateway.
    </li>
    <li>
      Verified the private route table contained no direct default route to the
      Internet Gateway.
    </li>
    <li>
      Reviewed Terraform outputs and AWS resource details to confirm the
      deployed topology matched the architecture documentation.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    End-to-end workload connectivity testing will be added when EC2 or other
    application resources are introduced in a later milestone.
  </p>
</section>

